<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-110-734  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 110 734.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Software  Jan 1989 v6 n1 p120(4).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Two CASE tools for the Macintosh. (Software Review)(computer-aided software engineering) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Yang, Sherry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Two effective computer-aided software engineering (CASE) productsfor the Macintosh computer, Advanced Logical Software's $925Anatool 3.0 structured systems-analysis tool and Iconix SoftwareEngineering's Power Tools 2.0 integrated CASE tool set, areevaluated.andP;  Anatool features a graphical interface, gooddocumentation, and three major components: dataflow-diagrameditor, data dictionary manager, and procedure specifications andutilities.andP;  Power Tools consists of five $995 tools (bundled for$4,495): the Free Flow structured systems-analysis tool; SmartChart, which combines a language-sensitive editor andstructure-chart generator; Power PDL, a program-design languageprocessor; ASCII Bridge, which imports and exports ASCII code toand from Free Flow; and the Fast Task graphical editor andstate-transition diagram generator.andP;  Anatool is preferred becauseof its ease of use and excellent documentation.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Power Tools 2.0 (Utility program)Anatool 3.0 (Program development software).andO;Topic:     EvaluationComputer-Aided Software EngineeringProgram Development Tools.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The Power Tools organization showing the interaction of its fivetools. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>